@Node "Introduction" "Charon.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Registration"
@Prev "Legal information"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction
************

   One of the Internet programs that Amiga was missing was a good
download manager. Or just any download manager, for that matter. As
author of HTTPResume, I got quite a few suggestions to make something
"like GetRight or Go!Zilla on the PC". So, as the need was obvious, I
slowly started working on it from the scratch.

   Charon is a download manager, plain and simple. You can use your
browser to download files, but they don't have enough options to
finetune the process. In order to have full control over downloads, you
need a download manager: something designed for that specific purpose.
This Charon, unlike mythical Charon who transfers souls of the dead
over the river Styx to the underworld, transfers files over the
Internet to your HD.

   What does it do?

   @{b}*@{ub} Multiple download of HTTP/HTTPS/FTP files all with/without proxy,
     with resume (if server supports it). HTTPS support using AmiSSL or
     MiamiSSL.

   @{b}*@{ub} Automatic retry/resume of downloads up to specified number of
     tries.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Huge@{ui} number of options to customise it as you wish including:
     setting timeout after which download is retried, setting minimum
     allowed number of CPS, maximum number of CPS...

   @{b}*@{ub} Scheduled downloads.

   @{b}*@{ub} Integrated Internet searches such as Aminet search, MP3 search etc.

   @{b}*@{ub} Has a HTML parser window which shows all links in a file.

   @{b}*@{ub} It can automatically choose proxy based on your hostname or IP
     address.

   @{b}*@{ub} ARexx interface.

   @{b}*@{ub} MUI GUI.


@EndNode

@Node "Registration" "Charon.guide/Registration"
@Next "Requirements"
@Prev "Introduction"
@Toc "Main"

Registration
************

   Charon is shareware. You are allowed to use evaluation version for
30 days and than you must either register or stop using it.  Registered
users will receive their personal key file which will enable them to
use all features of Charon. To see how to register, please visit Charon
home page (see @{"support" Link "Support"}).

   Evaluation version has following limitations:

   @{b}*@{ub} Only one copy of Charon can be started.

   @{b}*@{ub} There's maximum of two simultaneous downloads at the same time.

   @{b}*@{ub} "Max CPS" option can't be switched off and the fastest download
     speed is limited to 500 CPS.

   @{b}*@{ub} About window is opened at the start of the program and can't be
     closed until ten seconds have passed.


@EndNode

@Node "Requirements" "Charon.guide/Requirements"
@Next "Installation"
@Prev "Registration"
@Toc "Main"

Requirements
************

   @{b}*@{ub} An AmiTCP compatibile TCP/IP stack such as Miami or Genesis.

   @{b}*@{ub} AmiSSL or MiamiSSL packages for HTTPS transfers.

   @{b}*@{ub} MUI for graphic interface.

   @{b}*@{ub} Newest versions of NList and NListtree MUI custom classes by
     Carsten Scholling.


@EndNode

@Node "Installation" "Charon.guide/Installation"
@Next "Menus"
@Prev "Requirements"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
************

   To install Charon, please use the supplied Installer script.
Basically, it will copy the contents of the archive to a directory of
your choice and let you select what kind of pictures you want to use
for Charon's toolbar. You should already have NList and NListtree MUI
custom classes (which can be found on Aminet in dev/mui directory or on
author's homepage) in your @{b}MUI:Libs/MUI@{ub} directory for Charon to work.


@EndNode

@Node "Menus" "Charon.guide/Menus"
@Next "Settings"
@Prev "Installation"
@Toc "Main"

Menus
*****

   Here's a short description of all menu items:

@{b}Project/Entries/New URL...@{ub}
     Opens a window in which a new URL can be created. The new URL will
     be placed into a group in which the indicator for the active entry
     currently resides and that group's settings will be used as default
     settings for the URL. Changing the group into which the URL should
     be placed @{i}does not@{ui} copy that group's settings automatically, @{b}Copy
     this group's settings@{ub} will do that.

@{b}Project/Entries/New group...@{ub}
     Opens a window in which a new group can be created. Any URL created
     in this group will have this group's settings by default.

@{b}Project/Entries/New clipboard URL...@{ub}
     Similar to @{b}New URL@{ub}, but URL field will already be filled with
     contents of the clipboard.

@{b}Project/Entries/Start@{ub}
     Starts downloading selected URLs. If there's already maximum
     number of transfers going on, the one you started will be queued.
     You can't start locked URLs (the ones that are underlined). Using
     start on a group is the same as starting all that group's entries.

@{b}Project/Entries/Stop@{ub}
     Stops downloading selected URLs. Using stop on a group is the same
     as stopping all that group's entries.

@{b}Project/Entries/Stop started@{ub}
     Stops download of started downloads.

@{b}Project/Entries/Edit...@{ub}
     Opens windows that enables you to edit selected groups and URLs.
     You can't edit locked entries.

@{b}Project/Entries/Remove@{ub}
     Removes selected groups and URLs from the list. If necessary, some
     downloads will be stoped.

@{b}Project/Entries/Schedule@{ub}
     Schedules selected URLs for download at specified time. You can't
     schedule locked URLs.

@{b}Project/Select/All@{ub}
     Selects all entries.

@{b}Project/Select/None@{ub}
     Deselects all entries.

@{b}Project/Select/Toggle@{ub}
     Selects entries that were not selected and vice versa.

@{b}Project/Select/Started@{ub}
     Selects started URLs.

@{b}Project/Import list...@{ub}
     Imports list of entries to download from a file. This file can be
     created by the @{b}Export list...@{ub} menu entry.

@{b}Project/Export list...@{ub}
     Exports the list of entries in the main window to a file in a
     format that Charon understands.

@{b}Project/Export list over...@{ub}
     Exports the list of entries in the main window to a file in a
     format that Charon understands, overwriting the old file.

@{b}Project/About...@{ub}
     Opens a window with information on Charon.

@{b}Project/About MUI...@{ub}
     Opens a window with information on MUI.

@{b}Project/Iconify...@{ub}
     Hides the Charon window either as an icon on the Workbench screen
     or as the Workbench "Tools" menu (selectable in MUI preferences).

@{b}Project/Quit@{ub}
     Exits Charon. All downloads will be stoped and the list of entries
     will be exported to the @{b}PROGDIR:Charon.list@{ub} file.

@{b}Windows/Active downloads...@{ub}
     Opens the window which shows the list of the active downloads.

@{b}Windows/Internet search...@{ub}
     Opens the window in which various Internet searches can be
     performed.

@{b}Windows/HTML links...@{ub}
     Opens the window which extracts URLs from a file.

@{b}Windows/Download log...@{ub}
     Opens a window which lists all files downloaded during the current
     session.

@{b}Windows/Information...@{ub}
     Opens the window with some information about the downloads.

@{b}Settings/Settings...@{ub}
     Opens the @{"settings" Link "Settings"} window.

@{b}Settings/Save settings as...@{ub}
     Saves the settings under a filename that you choose.

@{b}Settings/Save settings as default@{ub}
     Saves the settings as @{b}PROGDIR:Charon.cfg@{ub}.

@{b}Settings/Load settings...@{ub}
     Loads settings from a file that you choose.

@{b}Settings/Load default settings@{ub}
     Load the settings from @{b}PROGDIR:Charon.cfg@{ub}.

@{b}Settings/MUI...@{ub}
     Opens the MUI settings for Charon.

@{b}ARexx/Execute ARexx script...@{ub}
     Starts a specified ARexx script.


@EndNode

@Node "Settings" "Charon.guide/Settings"
@Next "ARexx interface"
@Prev "Menus"
@Toc "Main"

Settings
********

   Settings window has five pages (two of those are divided in two
parts).  Names in the brackets next to option names are significant
only to ARexx programmers.

@{b}Global@{ub}
     These are global settings that affect every URL or behaviour of
     the program itself.

        @{b}*@{ub} Base directory (STARTDIR) When you enter a URL, Charon will
          try to create the output file name using this value and the
          filename from the URL. For example, if you set the base
          directory to @{b}Downloads:@{ub} and enter a URL
          @{b}http://www.somehost.net/file.lha@{ub}, Charon will automatically
          fill in @{b}Downloads:file.lha@{ub} as the output file name. Note that
          you have to press @{b}enter@{ub} in the URL field for Charon to do
          this.

        @{b}*@{ub} Error sound (ERRORSOUND) This is the sound Charon will play
          when error is encountered during download of the file.

        @{b}*@{ub} Finished sound (FINISHEDSOUND) This is the sound Charon will
          play when a transfer is finished.

        @{b}*@{ub} Finished all sound (FINISHEDALLSOUND) This is the sound
          Charon will play when all started transfers are finished.

        @{b}*@{ub} On start execute (STARTSCRIPT) and On exit execute
          (STOPSCRIPT) These two specify commands which will be
          executed on program start/exit.  These commands are executed
          @{i}synchronously@{ui}, ie. Charon will not continue until they
          return. If start script returns an error, @{i}Charon will not
          start@{ui}. These scripts can be useful for starting/stopping
          TCP/IP stack or something similar.

        @{b}*@{ub} Edit script (EDITSCRIPT) When you edit a URL in the edit
          window and click @{b}OK@{ub} or @{b}OK & start@{ub}, the URL is locked and this
          script called @{i}asynchronously@{ui} with the following arguments: @{b}ID
          x ERROR y URL "http://www.some.url/" START z PORT port@{ub} ID is
          the ID of the download, error is always 0 for now, @{b}port@{ub} is
          name of the Charon's ARexx port that called the script. If
          @{b}START@{ub} is non-zero you should start the download using @{b}START@{ub}
          command after you have done everything you wanted (including
          unlocking the URL using @{b}UNLOCKURL@{ub} command!). See the example
          ARexx script that comes in the Charon archive. As of Charon
          v1.98, there can also be a @{b}GROUP@{ub} switch which specifies that
          a group is being edited and not a URL.

        @{b}*@{ub} Convert from (CONVFROM) and Convert to (CONVTO) These options
          can be used to convert some characters in the filename.  For
          example, setting @{b}Convert from@{ub} to "a" and @{b}Convert to@{ub} to "b"
          would convert all letters "a" to "b". This is case sensitive!
          If lengths of these values are not equal, both values will be
          cleared (it is not possible to check this from ARexx, so be
          careful when you do this)! Common use for this is to change
          spaces to underscores or something similar.

        @{b}*@{ub} Max transfers (MAXTRANSFERS) This sets maximum number of
          transfers that Charon will do at the same time. If more
          transfers are started, they will be queued.

        @{b}*@{ub} Max filename length (MAXNAMELEN) This lets you limit length
          of the filename. Note that if you set this to @{b}x@{ub} characters,
          Charon will copy first @{b}x@{ub} - 3 characters and use the URL to
          calculate the last three characters. This should make sure
          that you can use maximum filename length that your filesystem
          allows and that @{b}http://some.host.net/verylongfilename1@{ub} and
          @{b}http://some.host.net/verylongfilename2@{ub} don't end up with the
          same filename.

        @{b}*@{ub} Backup interval (BACKUPINTERVAL) If this is different from 0,
          Charon will backup its download list to directory @{b}Backup@{ub}
          every @{i}x@{ui} minutes.

        @{b}*@{ub} No safety requesters (NOSAFEREQUESTERS) This disables those
          "Are you sure?" requesters which are annoying to some people.

        @{b}*@{ub} Auto start (AUTOSTART) If set, automatically starts
          downloading URL as soon as you enter it (or queues it). Also,
          when you start Charon, it will automatically start/queue all
          downloads (except scheduled ones).

        @{b}*@{ub} Auto exit (AUTOEXIT) If all URLs are downloaded (there are no
          more entries in the list) and this option is set, Charon will
          exit.

        @{b}*@{ub} Don't load list (NOLOADLIST) Normally, Charon loads a list of
          URLs that it weren't downloaded the last time. If you don't
          want this to happen, you can set this option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Don't save list (NOSAVELIST) If you set this, Charon won't
          save URLs that were left in the list on exit.

        @{b}*@{ub} Delete files (DELETEFILES) If you think that @{b}Remove URL@{ub}
          should remove not only URL(s) from the list, but also actual
          file(s) from the disk, set this option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Show full URL (SHOWFULLURL) This controls whether the full
          URL or just the file part of the URL is displayed.

        @{b}*@{ub} Close gadget iconifies (CLOSEISICONIFY) Clicking on the
          window's close gadget will iconify Charon instead of quitting
          it. Change of this option doesn't take effect until you
          restart Charon!

        @{b}*@{ub} Always find proxy (ALWAYSFINDPROXY) Normally, Charon uses the
          list of proxies that you supply only when a new URL is
          created. If you want it to check which proxy to use whenever
          a download starts, check this option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Show gadgets as (TOOLBARTYPE) You can select whether you want
          toolbar buttons to be shown as pictures, pictures and text or
          just text.

@{b}Proxies@{ub}
     These settings allow Charon to automatically choose proxy based on
     your hostname or IP address. When Charon wants to find out which
     proxy to use, it starts from the beginning of the list and checks
     if your hostname/IP address matches pattern in the left column of
     the list. If it does, Charon will use the corresponding proxy from
     the right column of the list. @{b}Proxy list@{ub} (PROXIES) string gadget
     should contain name of the file where these settings will be saved.

@{b}Local@{ub}
     Here you can set default settings for every URL from root group.
     Settings for URLs from specific group are kept in the group itself
     and should be edited there.

        @{b}*@{ub} Proxy (PROXY) Proxy server. Most of the time it's something
          like @{b}http://proxy.mydomain.net:8080/@{ub} or similar.

        @{b}*@{ub} Download attempts (DOWNLOADATTEMPTS) How many times should
          Charon try to download this URL before it gives up?

        @{b}*@{ub} Download delay (RETRYDELAY) Specifies how many seconds should
          Charon wait before it retries the download of this URL.

        @{b}*@{ub} Timeout (resumable) (TIMEOUTRES) If resumable download stops
          for this many seconds, Charon will stop it and then start it
          again. Zero means no timeout.

        @{b}*@{ub} Timeout (not resumable) (TIMEOUTNRES) If non-resumable
          download stops for this many seconds, Charon will stop it and
          try it again. Zero means no timeout.

        @{b}*@{ub} Max timeouts (MAXTIMEOUTS) One timeout is not regarded as
          error. If @{b}Max timeouts@{ub} occur, it will be regarded as @{i}one@{ui}
          error.

        @{b}*@{ub} Max CPS (MAXCPS) If you are f. ex. chatting on IRC and you
          don't want all bandwidth eaten up by file downloads, you can
          limit the speed of the transfer.

        @{b}*@{ub} Min CPS (resumable) (MINCPSRES) If resumable download gets
          too slow, Charon will stop it and retry.

        @{b}*@{ub} Min CPS (not resumable) (MINCPSNRES) If non-resumable
          download gets too slow, Charon will stop it and retry.

        @{b}*@{ub} Ignore CPS (IGNORECPS) Some servers need a few seconds to
          really start transfering files properly. In order to prevent
          @{b}Min CPS@{ub} option from stopping the download too early, before
          it actually got started, this options specifies how many
          seconds to ignore the @{b}Min CPS@{ub} option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Directory structure (TREE) This allows you to preserve
          directory structure from the URL.  The behaviour of this
          option was changed when Charon v1.98 was released.  Setting
          this option to 0 and trying to download
          @{b}http://www.aminet.net/pub/aminet/comm/irc/amirc.lha@{ub} will make
          Charon append @{b}www.aminet.net/pub/aminet/comm/irc/amirc.lha@{ub} to
          the @{b}Base directory@{ub}. The setting of 1 would make it append
          @{b}pub/aminet/comm/irc/amirc.lha@{ub}. Directories that don't exist
          @{i}will be created@{ui}! If this option is set to -1, it will be
          ignored.

        @{b}*@{ub} Rollback (ROLLBACK) It can happen sometimes that proxy
          appends some bogus data when its link to the server that the
          file is on is interrupted. To prevent this, you can set
          rollback option and when error occurs Charon will ignore last
          @{i}x@{ui} bytes from the downloaded file and download them again to
          ensure that they are downloaded properly.

        @{b}*@{ub} Read buffer (READBUFFERLEN) This is the buffer that Charon
          uses for reading data from network.  If you have a modem
          connection (upto 56k), there's no point in increasing this
          value from default 10 kB. On the other hand, if you have
          faster connection (ISDN or similar) you will probably want to
          increase this value. See also @{b}DOS buffer@{ub} option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Write buffer (WRITEBUFFERLEN) This is the buffer that Charon
          uses for sending data to network.  The default 1 kB is quite
          sufficient and you don't need to increase it, no matter how
          fast your connection is.

        @{b}*@{ub} DOS buffer (DOSBUFFERLEN) This is the DOS buffer that Charon
          will set for the file it's downloading. If you think that
          Charon is writing to disk too often, increase this value. If
          you increase the length of the buffer, the upside is that
          Charon will write to disk less often and in larger chunks.
          But, if you set it too high (say 100 kB) and your computer
          crashes for some reason, contents of that buffer won't be
          written to disk! This option is available only if you have
          OS3.1 or higher.

        @{b}*@{ub} Before download start (BEFORESCRIPT) and After download end
          (AFTERSCRIPT) These commands are executed @{i}asynchronously@{ui}
          before (after) the download is started (finished) with the
          following arguments: @{b}ID x ERROR y URL "http://www.some.url/"@{ub}
          ID is the ID of the download (only useful in ARexx scripts).
          In "before script", ERROR is always 0 and ID can be used for
          QUERYing URLs attributes. In "after script" ID is only valid
          if ERROR is not 0, ie. the URL will stay in the list. Note
          that the URL is quoted.

        @{b}*@{ub} No proxy (NOPROXY) Don't use proxy even if it's specified.

        @{b}*@{ub} Overwrite (OVERWRITE) Always start downloading file from
          scratch, never try to resume.

        @{b}*@{ub} Don't keep date (NOKEEPDATE) Charon normally tries to find
          out date of the file on server and keep it the same on the
          local file. If you don't want that to happen, switch this on.

        @{b}*@{ub} Force comment (FORCECOMMENT) When Charon downloads a file, it
          writes the URL to its comment, but only if it didn't already
          have it. If you want Charon to always write the comment to
          the output file, you should set this option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Owerwrite if no resume (OVERWRITEIFNORESUME) Charon will
          always try to resume interrupted transfers. However, some
          servers don't support resume and Charon will then report
          fatal error.  If you want it to restart downloading file from
          scratch instead, set this option. @{i}Overwrite will
          automatically be set in this case@{ui}.

@{b}HTTP@{ub}
     Everything said for @{b}Local@{ub} settings applies here to. These are some
     settings specific to HTTP transfers (this also includes those that
     go through proxy).

        @{b}*@{ub} Referer (REFERER) This sets @{b}Referer:@{ub} HTTP header field. Some
          sites allow download only if link to the file was on their
          HTML page. When you click on a link on a page, browsers send
          URL of that page in @{b}Referer:@{ub} field (unless you turn it off).
          Charon doesn't send @{b}Referer:@{ub} field by default, but if you
          find a link that requires this field, use this option to set
          it. This field will always be sent until you clear it.
          Typically, @{b}Referer:@{ub} field for f. ex.
          @{b}http://www.host.com/dir/dir1/dir2/file.ext@{ub} should be
          @{b}http://www.host.com/@{ub} or @{b}http://www.host.com/dir1/dir2/@{ub}.  See
          also @{b}Auto Referer: field@{ub} option.

        @{b}*@{ub} User-Agent (USERAGENT) This sets @{b}User-Agent:@{ub} HTTP header
          field. You should very rarely need to change this. Some
          servers send the same @{i}HTML@{ui} pages to browsers differently
          depending on @{b}User-Agent:@{ub} field ("This works in Netscape, this
          in Explorer..."). If you don't know anything about this, you
          don't need to use it.

        @{b}*@{ub} No cache (NOCACHE) There are some stupid proxy servers that
          don't check if the copy of the file they have cached is up to
          date. In that case, you can force them to fetch it from the
          original server again.

        @{b}*@{ub} Date check (DATECHECK) If you want Charon to check whether
          partial copy of the file is older than the one on the server
          (f. ex. if the copy on the server was changed in the mean
          time) you can switch this on. However, because of daylight
          savings time, inaccurate clocks and many other things, this
          might not work as expected.

        @{b}*@{ub} Only if updated (ONLYIFUPDATED) If you are making a mirror of
          a site, you will probably want to download a file only if
          it's updated, ie. if your copy is older than the one on the
          server. In that case you should switch this option on. @{i}This
          option is valid only in combination with@{ui} @{b}Overwrite@{ub} @{i}option@{ui}!
          Also, you @{i}shouldn't@{ui} use @{b}Don't keep date@{ub} option.

        @{b}*@{ub} Auto Referer: field (AUTOREFERER) If this is set, Charon will
          automatically change and send @{b}Referer:@{ub} HTTP field with every
          request. This might be neccesary since many servers now allow
          download only if request for the file has appropriate
          Referer: field, otherwise they usually redirect you to their
          main page. See also @{b}Referer:@{ub} option.

@{b}FTP@{ub}
     Everything said for @{b}Local@{ub} settings applies here to. These are some
     settings specific to FTP transfers (those that don't go through
     proxy).

        @{b}*@{ub} No "PORT" Charon normally sets up FTP transfers using @{b}PASV@{ub}
          command which has some advantages over @{b}PORT@{ub} command. In case
          @{b}PASV@{ub} doesn't work, Charon will fall back to @{b}PORT@{ub} command.
          However, if you are on a firewall, this definitely won't work
          and will block for some time. If this happens to you with
          every FTP server, switch this on. Note that there are some
          firewalls whose purpose is not to let you use direct FTP
          downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} FTP e-mail Anonymous FTP servers require you to send your
          e-mail address as password. However, you shouldn't need to
          use your real e-mail address, you can put anything you want
          here. Some servers perform more or less complex checks, so
          sometimes you might need to use at least domain part of your
          e-mail address (after "@" sign).


@EndNode

@Node "ARexx interface" "Charon.guide/ARexx interface"
@Next "Advanced"
@Prev "Settings"
@Toc "Main"

ARexx interface
***************

   Charon's ARexx port is called CHARON.@{b}x@{ub} where @{b}x@{ub} depends on number of
instances of Charon that are started. Entries in the list are
references by @{b}ID@{ub}s which can be gotten in numerous ways. In addition to
standard MUI ARexx commands, Charon defines the folowing commands:

@{b}@{b}NEWURL@{ub} - Inserts a new URL into the list@{ub}
     Template: NEWURL URL/A,FILE,GROUP/N,LOCK/S

     Inserts a new @{b}URL@{ub} into the specified @{b}GROUP@{ub}. If URL is string
     @{b}clipboard@{ub}, it will be read from clipboard. If group is omitted,
     the URL will be added into the root group. RESULT will have ID of
     the new URL or 0 if it couldn't have been created. @{b}FILE@{ub} is the
     output file. If it is not given, Charon will try to construct it
     using @{b}Base directory@{ub} and filename from URL. @{b}LOCK@{ub} optionally locks
     the URL which prevents it from being edited, started (f. ex. by
     @{b}AUTOSTART@{ub} option).

@{b}@{b}NEWGROUP@{ub} - Inserts a new group into the list@{ub}
     Template: NEWGROUP NAME/A,OPEN/S,LOCK/S

     Inserts a new group with specified name into the list. You can use
     @{b}OPEN@{ub} switch to specify whether the group should be "open".  @{b}LOCK@{ub}
     optionally locks the group which prevents it from being edited.

@{b}@{b}START@{ub} - Starts download of specified URL(s)@{ub}
     Template: START ID/N,SELECTED/S,ALL/S

     Starts the specified URL(s). If you want to start specified URL
     you should specify its ID. @{b}SELECTED@{ub} switch starts only selected
     URLs, whilst @{b}ALL@{ub} switch starts all URLs. Locked URLs can't be
     started.  If @{b}ID@{ub} is ID of a group, all entries in that group will
     be started.

@{b}@{b}STOP@{ub} - Stops download of URL@{ub}
     Template: STOP ID/N,SELECTED/S,STARTED/S,ALL/S

     Stops the specified URL(s). Options are the same as in @{b}START@{ub}
     command.  If @{b}ID@{ub} is ID of a group, all entries in that group will
     be stopped.

@{b}@{b}EDIT@{ub} - Opens edit window for specified URL(s)@{ub}
     Template: EDIT ID/N,SELECTED/S,ALL/S

     Edits the specified groups and URLs. Options are the same as in
     @{b}START@{ub} command.

@{b}@{b}REMOVE@{ub} - Removes specified URL(s)@{ub}
     Template: REMOVE ID/N,SELECTED/S,ALL/S,FORCE/S

     Removes the specified groups and URLs from the list. @{b}FORCE@{ub} won't
     ask the user for confirmation even if "No safety requesters" is not
     checked. Other options are the same as in @{b}START@{ub} command.

@{b}@{b}SCHEDULE@{ub} - Schedules specified URL(s)@{ub}
     Template: SCHEDULE ID/N,SECONDS/N/A,SELECTED/S,ALL/S

     Schedules specified URL(s) to a date which is @{b}SECONDS@{ub} seconds
     after January 1st 1978. See also @{b}GETNUMSECONDS@{ub} ARexx command.

@{b}@{b}IMPORTLIST@{ub} - Imports list of URLs@{ub}
     Template: IMPORTLIST NAME/A

     Imports list of URLs in format that Charon understands. @{b}NAME@{ub} is
     the name of the file which contains the list.

@{b}@{b}EXPORTLIST@{ub} - Exports list of URLs@{ub}
     Template: EXPORTLIST NAME/A,OVERWRITE/S

     Exports list of URLs to a file named @{b}NAME@{ub}. If @{b}OVERWRITE@{ub} is used,
     the file will be overwriten with the new one.

@{b}@{b}LOCKURL@{ub} - Forbids changes to/starting/scheduling etc. of group or URL@{ub}
     Template: LOCKURL ID/N/A

     Locks group or URL with specified @{b}ID@{ub}. This prevents URLs from being
     changed, scheduled or started etc.

@{b}@{b}UNLOCKURL@{ub} - Removes the lock from group or URL@{ub}
     Template: UNLOCKURL ID/N/A

     This command is reverse to @{b}LOCKURL@{ub} command.

@{b}@{b}GETFIRSTURL@{ub} - Returns the ID of the first (selected) URL in the list@{ub}
     Template: GETFIRSTURL SELECTED/S

     Returns the ID of the first URL (or first selected URL) or 0 if
     the list is empty.

@{b}@{b}GETNEXTURL@{ub} - Returns the ID of next (selected) URL in the list@{ub}
     Template: GETNEXTURL ID/N/A,SELECTED/S

     Returns the ID of the URL which is after the one with ID @{b}ID@{ub} (or of
     the next selected URL) or 0 if it's the last (selected) one in the
     list.

@{b}@{b}GETPREVURL@{ub} - Obsolete as of Charon v1.98@{ub}
     Template: GETPREVURL ID/N/A,SELECTED/S

     This command is obsolete and nonexistant as of Charon v1.98.

@{b}@{b}GETLASTURL@{ub} - Obsolete as of Charon v1.98@{ub}
     Template: GETLASTURL SELECTED/S

     This command is obsolete and nonexistant as of Charon v1.98.

@{b}@{b}GETFIRSTGROUP@{ub} - Returns the ID of the first (selected) group in the list@{ub}
     Template: GETFIRSTGROUP SELECTED/S

     Returns the ID of the first (selected) group or 0 if there are no
     (selected) groups.

@{b}@{b}GETNEXTGROUP@{ub} - Returns the ID of next (selected) group in the list@{ub}
     Template: GETNEXTGROUP ID/N/A,SELECTED/S

     Returns the ID of the group which is after the one with the ID of
     @{b}ID@{ub} (or of the next selected group) or 0 if it's the last
     (selected) group in the list.

@{b}@{b}GETURLSTATE@{ub} - Returns the state of the URL@{ub}
     Template: GETURLSTATE ID/N/A

     Returns state of URL with specified @{b}ID@{ub}. Possible responses are
     "LOCKED", "READY", "QUEUED", "DOWNLOADING", "ERROR" and
     "SCHEDULED".

@{b}@{b}QUERY@{ub} - Querries some attributes of the group/URL@{ub}
     Template: QUERY ID/N/A,OPTION/A/F

     Queries state of a URL option with specified @{b}ID@{ub}. @{b}ID@{ub} of 0 specifies
     default options (ie. default ones for new URL). Also, use 0 to get
     global options (MAXTRANSFERS etc). For possible values for @{b}OPTION@{ub},
     see @{"settings" Link "Settings"}. Other possible values are:

        @{b}*@{ub} VERSION Returns version of Charon.

        @{b}*@{ub} STARTEDTRANSFERS Returns number of currently started
          transfers.

        @{b}*@{ub} NUMTRANSFERS Returns number of entries in the list.

        @{b}*@{ub} URL Returns URL of the specified transfer.

        @{b}*@{ub} FILE Returns name of the output file of the specified
          transfer.

        @{b}*@{ub} TRANSFERREDLENGTH Data downloaded so far.

        @{b}*@{ub} FULLLENGTH Length of the file on server or 0 if server sent
          no information about it.

        @{b}*@{ub} SCHEDULE Returns how many seconds from January 1st 1978 is
          transfer scheduled after.

     If @{b}ID@{ub} is the ID of a group, @{b}OPTION@{ub} can also be:

        @{b}*@{ub} NAME Returns the name of the group.

@{b}@{b}SET@{ub} - Sets some of the options for URL@{ub}
     Template: SET ID/N/A,OPTION/A/F

     Sets state of a URL option with specified @{b}ID@{ub}. @{b}ID@{ub} of 0 specifies
     default options (ie. default ones for new URL). Also, use 0 to set
     global options (MAXTRANSFERS etc). You can't change locked or the
     one that is being downloaded. For possible values for @{b}OPTION@{ub}, see
     @{"settings" Link "Settings"}. Other possible values are:

        @{b}*@{ub} URL Sets URL of the specified transfer.

        @{b}*@{ub} FILE Sets name of the output file of the specified transfer.

     If @{b}ID@{ub} is the ID of a group, @{b}OPTION@{ub} can also be:

        @{b}*@{ub} NAME Sets the name of the group.

@{b}@{b}GETNUMSECONDS@{ub} - Returns number of seconds that passed up to specified date@{ub}
     Template: GETNUMSECONDS DATE

     Returns number of seconds that passed between January 1st 1978 and
     given date. Empty @{b}DATE@{ub} is the same as current date.  Otherwise, it
     should be in format day:month:year:hour:minute:second.  F. ex. if
     you want to be the first one who asks for a transfer in the next
     millenium, you would ask for @{b}GETNUMSECONDS 1:1:2001:00:00:00@{ub} and
     forward the result to SCHEDULE command.

@{b}@{b}FINDURLBYID@{ub} - Checks whether a URL with the given ID is in the list@{ub}
     Template: FINDURLBYID ID/N/A

     Finds URL with specified @{b}ID@{ub} and returns 1 if it's in the list or 0
     if it was not found. Useful if you want to see if the URL with the
     @{b}ID@{ub} you have is still in the list.

@{b}@{b}FINDGROUPBYID@{ub} - Checks whether a group with the given ID is in the list@{ub}
     Template: FINDGROUPBYID ID/N/A

     Same as FINDURLBYID, but for groups.

@{b}@{b}FINDGROUPBYNAME@{ub} - Searches for the group with the specified name@{ub}
     Template: FINDGROUPBYNAME NAME/A

     Searches for the group with the specified name (case insensitive)
     and returns its ID if one is found, or 0 otherwise.

@{b}@{b}SELECT@{ub} - Selects group of URLs@{ub}
     Template: SELECT TYPE/A

     Selects group of URLs by specified @{b}TYPE@{ub}. @{b}TYPE@{ub} is one of ALL, NONE,
     TOGGLE, STARTED.

@{b}@{b}HTMLLINKSWINDOW@{ub} - Opens HTML parser window@{ub}
     Template: HTMLLINKSWINDOW FILE/A,BASEURL/A

     Opens a window which extracts links from a HTML file and sets file
     and base URL fields.

@{b}@{b}BACKUP@{ub} - Forces a backup of the list file@{ub}
     Template: BACKUP

     Forces a backup of the list file.

@{b}@{b}TOGGLEMAINWINDOW@{ub} - Hides/shows the main window@{ub}
     Template: TOGGLEMAINWINDOW

     This function hides/shows the main window. If it is open, there are
     no additional windows from Windows menu opened and TOGGLEMAINWINDOW
     is issued, the application will be iconified.

@{b}@{b}SETAUTHORIZATION@{ub} - Sets/changes username/password in a URL@{ub}
     Template: SETAUTHORIZATION ID/N/A,USERNAME/A,PASSWORD

     This functions sets username and password in a URL. If URL already
     has username and password in it, they will be replaced. As of v1.4,
     Charon accepts SETAUTHORISATION as synonym for SETAUTHORIZATION.


@EndNode

@Node "Advanced" "Charon.guide/Advanced"
@Next "Tips and tricks"
@Prev "ARexx interface"
@Toc "Main"

Advanced
********

   As of Charon v1.98, there are some new options which are inaccessible
though the GUI:

   @{b}*@{ub} Charon has two tooltypes/CLI arguments, @{b}SETTINGS@{ub} and @{b}LOG@{ub}. The
     @{b}SETTINGS@{ub} tooltype/argument specifies what configuration should
     Charon load instead of @{b}PROGDIR:Charon.cfg@{ub}.  The @{b}LOG@{ub}
     tooltype/argument specifies the name of the file into which it
     should log the download events. If no argument to this option is
     given, the default is something like @{b}T:Charon.debug.xxxxxxxx@{ub}.

   @{b}*@{ub} If a file named PROGDIR:Config/HTTPHeadersLog exists, Charon will
     read first line from that file to get a name of the file to which
     it will write all the HTTP headers that it sends and receives.
     This should be something like CON:... This option is mostly here
     for debugging.

   @{b}*@{ub} If there is a file named PROGDIR:Config/NoFilesizeCheck then
     Charon will not check the size of each file during the startup.
     This is useful if you have a very large list and it would take too
     much time to read the size of each file. However, if this option
     is used, size of the file on server also won't be shown (otherwise
     the percentage information would be wrong).


@EndNode

@Node "Tips and tricks" "Charon.guide/Tips and tricks"
@Next "History"
@Prev "Advanced"
@Toc "Main"

Tips and tricks
***************

   @{b}*@{ub} Entries in the main list are draggable. You can move them around
     and change the order of downloads and their groups as you wish.

   @{b}*@{ub} Looking for a MP3 file? Use Internet search window!

   @{b}*@{ub} If you use AWeb and you happen to be on a page from which you'd
     like to download heaps of links, you can use the supplied
     ShowLinks.rexx ARexx script to have them all presented to you.

   @{b}*@{ub} Edit URL window is an app window. You can drop icons on it and
     Charon will use name of that file. If the file has URL in its
     comment, that comment will be copied to the URL field.

   @{b}*@{ub} Edit URL window has a menu which will let you load a @{b}.cfg@{ub} file.
     You can create a @{b}.cfg@{ub} file if you choose @{b}Save settings as...@{ub} entry
     from Settings menu.

   @{b}*@{ub} When you enter URL in the Edit URL window, press @{b}enter@{ub} for Charon
     to automatically create filename from the URL.

   @{b}*@{ub} Use provided ARexx script to send links from browsers to Charon.

        @{b}*@{ub} In AWeb, go to Settings/GUI settings/Pop-up and an entry to
          each type. The name of the command can be f. ex. @{b}Download@{ub} and
          the command should be @{b}SYSTEM CharonPath:Rexx/AddURL.rexx
          "%u"@{ub}. This will download files to your default download
          directory.

        @{b}*@{ub} In IBrowse 2.2+, go to Preferences/Settings.../GUI/FAB menus,
          then drag Custom entry to each Link, Imagelink, Page and Image
          sections (you can then rename it if you want). Select ARexx
          in the cycle gadget and select AddURL.rexx script. In the
          argument field enter "%i", "%l" or "%u" to download image
          URL, link URL or page URL respectively.

        @{b}*@{ub} As far as I know, this functionality should now be available
          in Voyager, but I don't know the details.


@EndNode

@Node "History" "Charon.guide/History"
@Next "Support"
@Prev "Tips and tricks"
@Toc "Main"

History
*******

@{b}Version 1.98 (6.1.2002)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} Introduced the concept of groups. Now each URL can belong to
          a group and will take that group's settings as its default
          settings. A new URL is by default placed in the group in
          which the active entry indicator is currently found.

        @{b}*@{ub} Completely rewritten URL parsing routine which resulted in a
          large speed up. This speed up would be even larger, but the
          URL comparison routine was changed from simple string compare
          to full-blown URL comparison routine which works properly.

        @{b}*@{ub} Rewritten detection of duplicates in the list. The code is now
          much faster and works for any number of duplicates, unlike in
          the last version.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now remembers the length of the file on server and
          shows it all the time (if it is available).

        @{b}*@{ub} Many improvements and some fixes in the HTML parsing routine.

        @{b}*@{ub} Addressed some security issues.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's now a special treatment for %2F URL escape code (/)
          because there are some filesystems that allow / in a filename.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added support for ftp://.../file;type=x URLs.

        @{b}*@{ub} When automatically creating filenames from the URL, %xx
          sequences are now decoded.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's a @{"new section" Link "Advanced"} in the documentation describing some
          "hidden" features. Charon's tooltypes/arguments (@{b}LOG@{ub} and
          @{b}SETTINGS@{ub}) are documented there.

        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to log all HTTP headers that were sent or
          received through Charon for debugging purposes. More about
          this in the @{"advanced section" Link "Advanced"} of the manual.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's a new configuration option which tells Charon not to
          read the size of the files on the disk during the startup thus
          speeding it up. More about this in the @{"advanced section" Link "Advanced"} of
          the manual.

        @{b}*@{ub} DOS requesters are now blocked while the list of entries is
          being loaded in order to prevent a bunch of the "Please
          insert ..." requesters from a appearing if one of your drives
          is dismounted.

        @{b}*@{ub} New gadget "Move & start" in HTML links and Internet search
          windows.

        @{b}*@{ub} Changed the way Charon shortens the filenames when "Max
          filename length" option comes into action.

        @{b}*@{ub} Changed the way the "Directory structure" option works. It now
          also takes into consideration the name of the host.

        @{b}*@{ub} When a file is downloaded and Charon needs to check if there
          are any queued files to be started, they are first searched
          for in the same group in which the downloaded file was.

        @{b}*@{ub} Some changes in ARexx interface as a result of introduction
          of groups.

        @{b}*@{ub} Updated some and removed some searches from Internet search
          window.  Ideas for possible additions are welcome.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a bug in parsing dates in HTTP headers.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a rare bug in display of percentage of the downloaded
          file.

        @{b}*@{ub} Too long FTP paths would cause a crash while sending a
          request. Fixed.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a small memory leak during that occured only when Charon
          was started from the shell.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon would report that it couldn't resume a transfer when a
          file had already been downloaded fully.

        @{b}*@{ub} SET Arexx command wasn't working properly for ages, fixed.

@{b}Version 1.4 (31.7.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} Double click on an entry now starts downloading it
          immediately, regardless of "Maximum transfers" option (it
          acted just the same as "Start" button up to now).

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon sometimes wouldn't resolve numeric IP addresses
          properly.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added a gadget next to "Proxy" gadget which lists all proxies
          from "Proxies" page in settings window making it easy to set
          current proxy to one of those.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added few more error messages that better explain what went
          wrong while connecting to a host.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added workaround for some servers (or scripts) which send
          relative URLs in Location: header for redirection although
          HTTP standard specifically says that they have to be absolute.

        @{b}*@{ub} While working on the above problem, fixed a much worse bug in
          handling Location: headers that could even cause a crash.

        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to log into FTP servers which send their
          initial greeting using somewhat unusual (although perfectly
          legal) multiline response.

        @{b}*@{ub} HTML links parser erroneously treated "./" as "../"

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed display of remaining time (it actually showed total
          length of the transfer). If I find another bug connected to
          this, I will have to seriously consider becoming a circus
          clown.

        @{b}*@{ub} Most of numeric buttons in settings window have been changed
          to a special kind of numeric string gadgets. They allow input
          of numbers only in certain range and have bubble help to
          indicate which range is that.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option: "Always find proxy" tells Charon to always try to
          set the proxy based on your current IP address, not only when
          you create an entry for the first time.

        @{b}*@{ub} Del key is now shortcut for "Remove".

        @{b}*@{ub} HTML parser now ignores mailto: links.

        @{b}*@{ub} Active downloads window didn't update data percentage properly
          when the main window was hidden.

        @{b}*@{ub} Now removes "blah" out of http://www.host.com/file.html#blah
          user entered URLs (which it should have been doing since ages
          ago, argh).

        @{b}*@{ub} If "Directory structure" option is active (ie. it's not set to
          -1) and filename contains just name of directory, Charon will
          append index.html to it.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu item and ARexx option: "Export list over" which
          overwrites the file to which it writes the list instead of
          appending to it.

        @{b}*@{ub} Removed some space between settings pages and save/use/cancel
          gadgets in settings window which sometimes caused MUI to
          render it in a rather strange way.

        @{b}*@{ub} Moved "No proxy" gadget to Local1 page, next to "Proxy"
          gadget.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now sets busy pointer whenever a list is loaded or
          saved.

        @{b}*@{ub} Corrected spelling of ARexx command TRANSFEREDLENGTH to
          TRANSFERREDLENGTH. The old form is still accepted for
          compatibility rasons.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added SETAUTHORISATION as synonym for SETAUTHORIZATION ARexx
          command.

        @{b}*@{ub} Bubble help for main display which showed URL, proxy and
          percentage of an entry is now updated more regularly.

@{b}Version 1.3 (24.6.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} New option: Edit script. When you edit an entry in edit window
          and click OK or OK & start, this script will be called so you
          can change something in the entry (for example, set
          username/password, change proxy).

        @{b}*@{ub} Files from Backup directory are now automatically imported
          into Charon's main list.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed display of sizes/transfer rates of extremely large files
          (hopefuly for the last time).

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed crashes when changing Internet search engine. There was
          something really strange about this, I still think there was
          nothing wrong with Charon. Anyway, the fix definitely works.

        @{b}*@{ub} If server sends larger file than it indicated, Charon now acts
          as if no size was specified. This fixes problems with some bad
          servers.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed a pretty big bug: if the last entry in the list was
          selected and second entry from the end active, the whole list
          would be deleted!

        @{b}*@{ub} Faster adding of links from Internet search and HTML links
          window to main window.

        @{b}*@{ub} If an entry was downloading and was removed, queued file(s)
          that should have been started wouldn't be started.

        @{b}*@{ub} Made it impossible for older versions of Charon to open
          libraries of newer versions (since these are incompatible)
          just in case.

        @{b}*@{ub}     @{b}Select none@{ub} menu entry and ARexx command now also turn off
          the active entry.

        @{b}*@{ub} New ARexx command: SETAUTHORIZATION which sets username and
          password in a URL.

        @{b}*@{ub} Added an ARexx script to "pause" (actually to stop and then
          start) downloads until you, for example, collect your e-mail
          or something similar.

        @{b}*@{ub} Internal cleanups.

@{b}Version 1.2 (19.4.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to hide only main window and leave other
          windows open, f. ex. active downloads window.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option to make close window gadget act as iconify command.

        @{b}*@{ub} Finally properly fixed time remaining indicator.

        @{b}*@{ub} Somewhat undocumented tooltype/argument DEBUG has been changed
          to LOG which now optionally logs almost everything that
          happens while URL is downloaded.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed two bugs in HTML parsing, one of the two could be quite
          fatal at times (luckily, it would rarely happen).

        @{b}*@{ub} New ARexx command BACKUP which forces immediate backup of the
          list file.

        @{b}*@{ub} QUERY ARexx command now has two new arguments:
          TRANSFEREDLENGTH and FULLLENGTH.

@{b}Version 1.1 (24.3.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} New window for Internet searches. Currently, Aminet,
          AudioFind, MP3Box, Lycos MP3Search and Lycos FTPSearch
          searches are supported, but more searches are easy to add.

        @{b}*@{ub} New window which extracts all links from HTML file.

        @{b}*@{ub} New window that logs finished downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} New window that shows only active downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} New "minimal information" window that shows some info about
          the list of downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now optionally backs up its download list every x
          minutes.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option to execute a command when Charon is started and
          when it exits.

        @{b}*@{ub} It is now possible to execute a command before the download
          is started and after it's finished.

        @{b}*@{ub} New option: rollback which tries to prevent bad proxies from
          mangling the file which is being downloaded.

        @{b}*@{ub} There's a new option to make Charon show only filename part
          of the URL. This option is also accessible from the display's
          context menu.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now visually indicates when an entry with the same
          filename is entered.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu entry: stop started downloads.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu entries which make it possible to select all, toggle
          selected, select started entries. These options are also
          accessible from the display's context menu.

        @{b}*@{ub} New menu entry: New clipboard URL.

        @{b}*@{ub} New "paste from clipboard" gadget in edit window for those
          who are used to HTTPResume.

        @{b}*@{ub} Charon now uses Textinput MUI custom class by Oliver Wagner
          (if it's available) for its string gadgets.

        @{b}*@{ub} Corrected a problem which appeared when downloading from
          wu-ftpd-2.6.x FTP server.

        @{b}*@{ub} Edit window now has "OK & start" gadget.

        @{b}*@{ub} Bubble help for main list now gives some information about
          the currently active entry. This information is updated only
          when active entry is changed!

        @{b}*@{ub} Main window is now also an app window. It is also possible to
          drop icons on Charon's app icon when it's iconified.

        @{b}*@{ub} Width of the main list is now saved only on a window snapshot.

        @{b}*@{ub} Fixed the way time to end of the download was calculated.

        @{b}*@{ub} Settings window is rearranged.

        @{b}*@{ub} NEWURL ARexx command has new special URL called "clipboard"
          which gets it from the clipboard.

        @{b}*@{ub} Included ARexx example how to change an option for all
          selected URLs.

        @{b}*@{ub} Included ARexx script which shows all links on current HTML
          page in AWeb. Useful if you are on a ROM or picture gallery
          site and you want to download some links.

        @{b}*@{ub} ARexx commands are updated with new options.

@{b}Version 1.0 (3.2.2000)@{ub}
        @{b}*@{ub} First public release.


@EndNode

@Node "Support" "Charon.guide/Support"
@Next "Acknowledgements"
@Prev "History"
@Toc "Main"

Support
*******

@{b}Mailing list@{ub}
     For discussion about Charon you can join the Charon support mailing
     list. To join, send an e-mail to
     @{b}charon-list-subscribe@yahoogroups.com@{ub} .

@{b}WWW support site@{ub}
     Visit Charon WWW site at @{b}http://www.bigfoot.com/~TheAntony/Charon/@{ub}
     to get updates and support.

@{b}Author@{ub}
     If everything else fails, you can write to me directly.  E-mail:
     Andrija Antonijevic <TheAntony@bigfoot.com>.


@EndNode

@Node "Acknowledgements" "Charon.guide/Acknowledgements"
